Reddit Email 2K SharesThe Economist magazine published that there would be a world currency in place by 2018.
DEA OF SINGLE CURRENCY STARTED BACK IN 1988 AND WAS CALLED OUTLANDISH The idea of a single currency back in 1988 seemed to be outlandish.
The new single currency would see constraints on national governments being tightened.
Preparing for a single currency is going to ensure there are fewer pretend agreements on policy and there will be more real ones.
There will be active promotion of the private sectors use of international money along with any national money that exists.